    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-10-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-10-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="662"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d662">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.50 Recovery/9–949</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the ECA Administrator</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hoffman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-10-03">October 3,
                            1949</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Hoffman</hi>: The Department of State is grateful
                    for the comments contained in your letter of September 9 regarding the Chinese
                    Government’s request for economic aid which was submitted on August 15. The
                    Department is in agreement with the views expressed <pb facs="0707" n="697"
                        xml:id="pg_697"/> in your letter and believes that they represent a
                    comprehensive treatment of the question in its economic aspects. We are still
                    awaiting the comments of the Department of Defense on the Chinese requests for
                    military aid.<note n="2" xml:id="d662fn2">For reply from the Secretary of
                        Defense on October 14, see <ref target="#pg_551">p. 551</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Consideration continues to be given to the political and strategic factors
                    relating to Taiwan, and I hope that the Secretary or I will have an opportunity
                    to discuss with you the future of ECA’s operations on that island as soon as
                    there has been sufficient clarification of these aspects of the problem.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James</hi> E. <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
